HEADWORD: Cœlenterata
<hw>C⟦oe⟧*len`te*ra"ta</hw>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>koi^los</grk> hollow + <?/ intestines.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A comprehensive group of Invertebrata, mostly
marine, comprising the <class>Anthozoa</class>, <class>Hydrozoa</class>,
and <class>Ctenophora</class>. The name implies that the stomach and
body cavities are one. The group is sometimes enlarged so as to include
the sponges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coelenterate</ent>⟦br⟧
